---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="Steps to Opening a Daycare | Childcare Business Plan"
    description="Your path to opening a daycare depends on your state's licensing process and local requirements. Understand what affects your timeline and approach."
>
    <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-16 px-4">
        <!-- 1. OWNERSHIP FRAMING -->
        <section class="text-center mb-16">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                YOUR Path to Opening
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                Opening a daycare involves navigating state licensing, local
                regulations, and market preparation. The complexity and timeline
                of your journey depends entirely on where you're opening and
                what type of facility you're creating.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 2. FACTORS THAT AFFECT OUTCOME -->
        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                What Affects Your Timeline
            </h2>
            <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-600">
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Some states have streamlined licensing processes that take
                    weeks, while others involve months of paperwork,
                    inspections, and waiting periods. The type of facility
                    you're opening—home-based versus center-based—triggers
                    completely different regulatory pathways with different
                    complexity levels.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Your existing situation matters too. Do you already have a
                    suitable space or need to find one? Are you converting a
                    home or building out a commercial property? Is your local
                    market saturated or underserved? Each of these factors
                    changes which obstacles you'll face and in what order.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Local requirements layer on top of state regulations. Fire
                    marshal inspections, health department approvals, zoning
                    clearances, and business registrations all have their own
                    timelines and prerequisites. Your path isn't just different
                    from someone in another state—it's different from someone in
                    the next county.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 3. WHY GENERIC ADVICE FAILS -->
        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                Why Online Advice Often Conflicts
            </h2>
            <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-600">
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Generic timelines and step-by-step guides fall apart when
                    they hit your specific reality. An article that says
                    "getting licensed takes 3 months" might be right for one
                    state and completely wrong for yours. A checklist that
                    prioritizes finding a location first might waste your time
                    if your state requires pre-licensing training before you can
                    even apply.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    The order of operations matters enormously, and it's
                    determined by your state's licensing agency, your local
                    jurisdiction, and your business model. Following the wrong
                    sequence means redoing work, missing deadlines, or paying
                    for resources before you're ready to use them.
                </p>
                <p>
                    What you need isn't more generic advice—you need a roadmap
                    built on your state's specific requirements, your facility
                    type, and your current starting point. That level of
                    personalization is impossible to find in a one-size-fits-all
                    article.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 4. CTA TO CALCULATOR -->
        <section class="text-center py-12 px-8 glass-panel rounded-3xl">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                See How Much YOU Could Make in Your State
            </h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Before planning your path, understand your income potential
                based on your state's regulations.
            </p>
            <a
                href="/tools/income-builder"
                class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-teal-600 hover:bg-teal-700 text-white font-medium px-8 py-4 shadow-lg transition-all"
            >
                Use the Free Calculator →
            </a>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>
